<li id="cite_note-76"><b><a href="#cite_ref-76" title="">^</a></b> Duncan, J. Ligon 2003. "<a href="http://www.providencepca.com/essays/theonomy.html" class="external text" title="http://www.providencepca.com/essays/theonomy.html" rel="nofollow">The Westminster Confession of Faith: A Theonomic Document?</a>", 13 August 2003. Retrieved 6 October 2007.</li>
<li id="cite_note-77"><b><a href="#cite_ref-77" title="">^</a></b> Isbell, Sherman 1997. “The Divine Law of Political Israel Expired: <a href="http://www.members.aol.com/RSICHURCH/expire2.html" class="external text" title="http://www.members.aol.com/RSICHURCH/expire2.html" rel="nofollow">Part II</a> and <a href="http://www.members.aol.com/RSICHURCH/expire3.html" class="external text" title="http://www.members.aol.com/RSICHURCH/expire3.html" rel="nofollow">Part III</a>”. Retrieved 6 October 2007.</li>
<li id="cite_note-78"><b><a href="#cite_ref-78" title="">^</a></b> Poythress, Vern S. 1991. <i>The Shadow of Christ in the Law of Moses</i>. Brentwood TN: Wolgemuth &amp; Hyatt Publishers Inc.</li>
<li id="cite_note-79"><b><a href="#cite_ref-79" title="">^</a></b> Godfrey, W. Robert 1990, "Calvin and Theonomy," in <i>Theonomy: A Reformed Critique</i>, William S. Barker and W. Robert Godfrey eds., 299-312, (Grand Rapids, MI: Academie Books, 1990).</li>
<li id="cite_note-80"><b><a href="#cite_ref-80" title="">^</a></b> Ferguson, Sinclair 1990. "An Assembly of Theonomists?" in <i>Theonomy: A Reformed Critique</i>, William S. Barker and W. Robert Godfrey eds., 315-349, Grand Rapids, MI: Academie Books, 1990.</li>
</ol>
</div>
